      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AUXILIARY (3) is a former Victorian who was well supported for the new yard and led throughout at his NT debut to score an all-the-way win. This is tougher but drops in weight and small field suits. Take catching again. MONTJUIC MAGIC (6) is racing well with a fresh-up win then a narrow loss last time. Has speed and looks a place factor. BON'S PRIDE (2) settled last in open class latest but found the line strongly to just miss. Rates highly off that effort and will be tough to stop again. DOWN THE WICKET (5) ran third here last time behind AUXILIARY. Meets the winner 2.5kg better and drops significantly on the 60kg he carried last time. Worth including. BAHAMA BAY (1) is hard to fault, winning all three last campaign. Goes well fresh and capable of picking up where he left off.",
